articles.title: Part Missing On 737 MAX Plane In India, After Alaska Airlines' Mid-Air Scare - NDTV
articles.description: An inspection of all 40 Boeing 737 Max planes operated by Indian airlines found a missing part - a washer - on one aircraft, aviation regulator DGCA said Tuesday, prompting the American aerospace giant to sound a global call to scrutinise all planes.
